<br>
Rampage list gets set<br>
1) warrior 1<br>
2) warrior 2<br>
3) Monk 1<br>
4) Rogue 1<br>
5) Cleric 1<br>
<br>
so on and so forth.<br>
<br>
Lets say warrior 1 is the MT. So warrior 2 eats rampage as long as he is in melee range.<br>
<br>
Warrior 2 dies. Now the rampage list looks like this<br>
1) warrior 1<br>
2) Open slot<br>
3) Monk 1<br>
4) Rogue 1<br>
5) Cleric 1<br>
<br>
Warrior 1 is still the MT, so Monk 1 starts eatting rampages.<br>
<br>
Warrior 2 gets rezzed and goes back in to fight.  When he attacks and gets on IVs hate list, he falls into the highest open slot, ie slot 2 so your back to:<br>
1) warrior 1<br>
2) warrior 2<br>
3) Monk 1<br>
4) Rogue 1<br>
5) Cleric 1<br>
<br>
If wizard 1 had joined the raid late, and started nuking just after warrior 2 died, the rampage list would look like this<br>
1) warrior 1<br>
2) wizard 1<br>
3) Monk 1<br>
4) Rogue 1<br>
5) Cleric 1<br>
6) warrior 1<br>
<br>
Monk 1 would still continue to eat rampage, unless wizard 1 got in melee range.<br>
<br>
Thats how I believe it works <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=liziewurmscales>Lizie Wurmscales</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/9/03 9:13:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2589.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rampage</span><hr size=1> I've got a few comments on this. All of the information I mention in this thread will pertain to PoS mini bosses, because my guild has been busy with those lately and they are my most recent experience with rampage.<br>
<br>
I'm a Shadowknight, and I usually pull and RT for my guild.<br>
<br>
FD vs Rampage; We're in the desert, and we're pulling the mini who stands by those rocks with basically no guards. This is easy, but at the time I need to be afk, so I pull it, have SK2 shoot an arrow at him in mid pull (To set him just below me on Rampage list), and I feign once in camp. I come back about halfway through the fight, and ask SK2 how the rampage swap worked, he said he has had rampage the entire fight. Since I've never really tested rampage for myself before, I decided to. I got up from FD, SK2 was still taking rampage, I was meleeing and definately close enough to be taking rampage on this particular mob. Mini happened to rampage 3 times quickly, and SK2 went down. After that, I was back on rampage.<br>
<br>
Camping/Zoning/Dying/etc vs Rampage; Ok, this time we're in the Ocean camp. Recently I've been trying to pull minis without the need to clear the rest of the giants first, for the particular mini we were pulling (Whoever the Strong) I was using a bard with the new Lull song. I've used bards before and its worked great, the duration on the song is nice and long, and I've rarely had troubles. This was the first time that the bard had attempted to use lull for this mini. He was having some troubles and we ended up pulling the first room anyway. (For any of you who haven't seen it, this house has 2 rooms in it, front and back, the back has the mini and 3 guards.)  While trying to lull the back room, the bard got agro, the mini was among the mobs he agroed. (Note: bard was the first agro on the mini.) We eventually get the giants dead or lulled, and I pull. I was taking Rampage just as normal, bard was meleeing and was definately in rampage range.<br>
<br>
Now just yesterday, someone in /raidsay made the mistake of asking how exactly rampage worked, and how we were always able to determine I would have it ahead of time. Me and the guild's MT started explaining, but our views as far as FD/camping/memblur/zoning/etc differed. He swears by the information from this site, and I base my opinions off of my own experiences. I'll take what he says as truth most of the time, but in this case about changing rampage list my experience goes against what he says.<br>
<br>
I tried to be very detailed with my situations, and I'll try and keep up with this thread in case you guys have some comments. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior>The Steel Warrior</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena>The Arena</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.steelwarrior.org">The Steel Warrior website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.240<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

